About Us
Norbord Inc. is an international producer of wood-based panels with assets of US $1.6 billion. We have 17 plant locations in the United States, Europe and Canada.
We manufacture OSB in the United States, Canada and Europe. In addition, we manufacture MDF, particleboard and furniture in Europe.
Fast Facts
Based in Toronto, Canada
Common shares listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange (OSB:TSX and the New York Stock Exchange (OSB:NYSE))
Number of employees: 2,600
Operations:

15 OSB mills
1 MDF (medium density fibreboard) mill
2 particleboard mills
1 furniture plant

Applied Technology
Norbord’s technology group of scientists and engineers support our US, Canadian and European operations, contributing to our competitive strength in process and reliability improvement, product development and technology transfer.
Norbord’s technology staff is often found at various production facilities working as a team with mill personnel.
Norbord Technology is located at:
4960 Levy Street
Ville St. Laurent, Quebec
H4R 2P1
History



1987
Listed publicly on TSX as Noranda Forest Inc. (NF)


1988
Acquired Inverness OSB plant – UK´s first OSB operation


1989
Acquired Normick Perron sawmills and panel mills in northern Quebec and Ontario


1993
Divested 49% interest in MacMillan Bloedel for $594 million


1995
Completed construction on new greenfield OSB plant in Guntown, Mississippi, closely followed by a new OSB mill at La Sarre, Quebec
Formed joint venture with Glunz AG and became largest panel producer in UK


1998
Noranda Forest Inc. name changed to Nexfor Inc.


1999
Acquired 100% ownership in UK panel business
Sold 50% interest in Northwood Inc. for $170 million


2000
Opened OSB plant at Joanna, South Carolina
Acquired Juniper I-joist plant in New Brunswick


2001
Opened Barton OSB plant at Huguley, Alabama


2002
Acquired OSB mills in Cordele, Georgia; Jefferson, Texas;
Nacogdoches, Texas for $250 million


2003
Sold Quebec sawmills for pre-tax gain of $19 million


2004
Acquired remaining 50% of Bemidji OSB mill
Distributed paper, timberlands business to shareholders.
Nexfor Inc. renamed Norbord Inc. (NBD)
Acquired OSB/particleboard mill in Genk, Belgium for $64 million


2006
Began production on second OSB line at Cordele, Georgia


2007
Reached agreement to sell Juniper I- Joist Assets


2008
Confirmed closure of Particleboard Line at Genk, Belgium


2009
Formed a 50/50 Joint Venture hardwood plywood business with Kruger Inc.


2011
True North Hardwood Plywood Inc. announced the winding down of its hardwood plywood operation in Cochrane. Norbord held a 50% joint-venture interest in this non-core business.


2015
Merged with Ainsworth Lumber Co. Ltd., adding four OSB mills in 100 Mile House, British Columbia; Grande Prairie, Alberta; High Level, Alberta; and Barwick, Ontario


2016
Changed stock trading symbol on the Toronto Stock Exchange to OSB. Shares were also listed on the New York Stock Exchange on February 19, 2016 under the same symbol.
Reached agreement to exchange ownership of Val-d’Or, Quebec OSB mill for OSB mill in Chambord, Quebec












Norbord is a leading global manufacturer of wood-based panels with assets of US$1.8 billion and annual sales of approximately US$1.8 billion. Norbord has 17 operations in the United States, Europe and Canada.




