11
Managers




27
IT employees




$67.9MEST.
IT Budget




Norbord Inc. engages in the manufacture and sale of wood-based panels in North America and Europe. It offers oriented strand board (OSB), a structural engineered wood panel for construction and industrial use in the United States and Canada; and OSB,… MoreNorbord Inc. engages in the manufacture and sale of wood-based panels in North America and Europe. It offers oriented strand board (OSB), a structural engineered wood panel for construction and industrial use in the United States and Canada; and OSB, medium density fibreboard (MDF), and particleboard products for the construction, furniture, and do-it-yourself markets in Europe.
The IT department for international wood-based panels producer Norbord operates collectively out of the Toronto, ON office and the London, UK office.

Each office has teams responsible for IT Technical support including data security, telecommunications, data storage, desktop support, and hardware… MoreThe IT department for international wood-based panels producer Norbord operates collectively out of the Toronto, ON office and the London, UK office.

Each office has teams responsible for IT Technical support including data security, telecommunications, data storage, desktop support, and hardware and software support. Database Administrators oversee design, implementation, and maintenance of the company's Microsoft SQL Server and Access. 

Norbord uses Ivara's integrated enterprise asset management solutions to improve asset performance and reliability at its 12 mill locations in North America. The company uses Cisco CSA and Juniper Netscreen for IT security.





